# ELearning Platform — Project Notes

## Vision
A free, community-driven learning platform where users share downloadable resource links,
ask questions, and get answers — organized by subject area (Science, History, Math, etc.).
No selling. No file hosting. Users contribute external download links only.

---

## Recommended Website Structure

### Core Sections

1. **Home**
   - Featured resources
   - Trending questions/discussions
   - Subject category grid (Science, History, Math, Technology, Arts, etc.)
   - "How it works" intro for new visitors

2. **Resources Library**
   - Browse by category/subject
   - Each resource = title + description + external download link + uploader info
   - Filter by: subject, type (PDF, video link, eBook, etc.), date, popularity
   - Search bar
   - Users submit a link (Google Drive, Dropbox, Mega, etc.) — platform never stores the file

3. **Q&A / Forum (Blog-style)**
   - Subject-aligned sections (Science, History, Math, Language, etc.)
   - Users post questions with tags
   - Other users post answers; accepted answer marked by asker
   - Upvote/downvote system
   - Each subject has its own feed/board

4. **User Profiles**
   - Display name, subject interests/alignment
   - Resources they've shared
   - Questions asked & answers given
   - Reputation/contribution score

5. **Authentication**
   - Register / Login (email or OAuth)
   - Profile setup: choose subject alignments (shown on posts and recommendations)

6. **Admin Panel**
   - Report/flag system for bad links or spam
   - Category management
   - User moderation

---

## Page-Level Sitemap

```
/                          → Home
/resources                 → All resources
/resources/:category       → Resources filtered by subject (e.g. /resources/science)
/resources/:id             → Single resource detail page
/resources/submit          → Submit a new resource (link form)
/forum                     → All Q&A boards
/forum/:category           → Subject board (e.g. /forum/history)
/forum/:category/:post-id  → Single question + answers
/forum/ask                 → Post a new question
/profile/:username         → Public user profile
/dashboard                 → Private user dashboard
/login                     → Login page
/register                  → Register page
/admin                     → Admin panel (protected)
```

---

## Data Models (High-Level)

### User
- id, name, email, password (hashed)
- subjects[] (interests/alignment: Science, Math, etc.)
- role (user | moderator | admin)
- reputation score

### Resource
- id, title, description
- externalLink (URL to file — not stored on server)
- fileType (PDF, Video, eBook, etc.)
- category (subject)
- uploadedBy (user ref)
- createdAt, upvotes, downloads (click count)

### Post (Question)
- id, title, body
- category (subject)
- tags[]
- author (user ref)
- createdAt, views, upvotes

### Answer
- id, body
- postId (question ref)
- author (user ref)
- createdAt, upvotes, isAccepted (bool)

---

## Tech Stack Recommendation

### Frontend
- **Next.js** (React) — SSR for SEO, fast page loads
- **Tailwind CSS** — rapid styling
- **shadcn/ui** — component library

### Backend
- **Node.js + Express** — REST API
- **JSON file as database (temporary)** — see section below
- Swap to PostgreSQL + Prisma later with minimal code changes

### Auth
- **JWT tokens** stored in httpOnly cookies — works without a real DB
- Passwords hashed with **bcrypt** before writing to JSON

### Search
- In-memory filter over the JSON data (fast enough for small datasets)

### Hosting
- **Vercel** — frontend
- **Railway** or **Render** — Node.js backend (free tier)

---

## JSON File Database Strategy

### Why it works for now
- No setup, no cost, works offline
- Easy to inspect and edit manually
- Swap to a real DB later by replacing only the data-access layer

### File structure
```
server/
  data/
    users.json
    resources.json
    posts.json
    answers.json
```

### What each file looks like

**users.json**
```json
[
  {
    "id": "u1",
    "name": "Alice",
    "email": "alice@example.com",
    "passwordHash": "$2b$10$...",
    "subjects": ["Science", "Math"],
    "role": "user",
    "reputation": 0,
    "createdAt": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z"
  }
]
```

**resources.json**
```json
[
  {
    "id": "r1",
    "title": "Biology 101 Notes",
    "description": "Complete notes for intro biology",
    "externalLink": "https://drive.google.com/...",
    "fileType": "PDF",
    "category": "Science",
    "uploadedBy": "u1",
    "upvotes": 0,
    "downloads": 0,
    "createdAt": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z"
  }
]
```

**posts.json**
```json
[
  {
    "id": "p1",
    "title": "What is Newton's second law?",
    "body": "Can someone explain it with an example?",
    "category": "Science",
    "tags": ["physics", "newton"],
    "author": "u1",
    "upvotes": 0,
    "views": 0,
    "createdAt": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z"
  }
]
```

**answers.json**
```json
[
  {
    "id": "a1",
    "postId": "p1",
    "body": "F = ma. If you push a 2kg object with 10N, it accelerates at 5 m/s².",
    "author": "u2",
    "upvotes": 0,
    "isAccepted": false,
    "createdAt": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z"
  }
]
```

### How the data layer will be structured (easy to swap later)
```
server/
  db/
    index.js        ← exports read/write helpers (readJSON, writeJSON)
    users.js        ← all user queries (findByEmail, createUser, etc.)
    resources.js    ← all resource queries
    posts.js        ← all post queries
    answers.js      ← all answer queries
```

When switching to PostgreSQL, you replace only the files inside `server/db/`
and the rest of the app (routes, controllers) stays the same.

---

## Key Design Principles

- No file uploads — only external links (keeps storage costs zero)
- Subject alignment drives personalization (feed shows your subjects first)
- Community moderation (flag, report) to keep quality high
- Mobile-first layout
- SEO-friendly URLs for resource and forum pages

---

## Suggested Build Order (Phases)

**Phase 1 — Foundation**
- Auth (register/login + subject alignment setup)
- Subject categories seeded in DB
- Basic resource submission form (link + description + category)
- Resource browse/filter page

**Phase 2 — Community**
- Q&A forum with subject boards
- Post question, answer, accept answer
- Upvote system

**Phase 3 — Polish**
- User profiles and reputation
- Search across resources and forum
- Report/flag system
- Admin panel

**Phase 4 — Growth**
- Email notifications (new answers, trending resources)
- Bookmarks / saved resources
- Resource recommendations based on subject alignment
